{"id": "EUVD-2025-32867", "enisaUuid": "79cb4cf9-3009-3a4f-8f68-f33d4607bb41", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nrpmsg: char: Avoid double destroy of default endpoint\n\nThe rpmsg_dev_remove() in rpmsg_core is the place for releasing\nthis default endpoint.\n\nSo need to avoid destroying the default endpoint in\nrpmsg_chrdev_eptdev_destroy(), this should be the same as\nrpmsg_eptdev_release(). Otherwise there will be double destroy\nissue that ept->refcount report warning:\n\nrefcount_t: underflow; use-after-free.\n\nCall trace:\n refcount_warn_saturate+0xf8/0x150\n virtio_rpmsg_destroy_ept+0xd4/0xec\n rpmsg_dev_remove+0x60/0x70\n\nThe issue can be reproduced by stopping remoteproc before\nclosing the /dev/rpmsgX.", "datePublished": "2025-10-01T12:30:27", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-11T18:30:35", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50421", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3f20ef7a845c2c8d7ec82ecffa20d95cab5ecfeb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/467233a4ac29b215d492843d067a9f091e6bf0c5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ef828a39d6a7028836eaf37df3ad568c8c2dd6f9"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50421", "GHSA-7gv2-7hhr-4fm9"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "24b8e704-43e4-33fa-b269-c37ed966745b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "bea9b79c2d10fecf7bfa26e212ecefe61d232e39 <3f20ef7a845c2c8d7ec82ecffa20d95cab5ecfeb"}, {"id": "3ceede25-4e41-32cb-9a47-e3c039037dc7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "70e00fae-9f1c-3090-8833-c82753e94be9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "bea9b79c2d10fecf7bfa26e212ecefe61d232e39 <467233a4ac29b215d492843d067a9f091e6bf0c5"}, {"id": "878b78e2-9af6-3b00-85b0-d7b6ec75628c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.3"}, {"id": "92237e77-b4bf-3cd0-9351-1a30d2922e94", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.18"}, {"id": "a04f1382-afdc-311e-96